definition: Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing information about the Monitoring Programs originating source datasets. This table corresponds to the Record table in the database (.accdb) file.
A unique identifier assigned to the originating source data's program.
A bibliographic reference for the resource as a statement indicating how this record should be cited (attributed) when used.
NAdefinition: There is no formal citation for this dataset.

definition: URL identifier for the collection or dataset from which the record was derived. The source location for the originating source data or program website.
The name of the originating data set from which the record was derived.
The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.
URL identifier for the metadata for the originating source dataset or note how to access metadata.
URL identifier for access to the code used to pre-process (download, standardize and tidy) the data sets before integration into the destination dataset.
NAdefinition: Pre-processing code was not used for this dataset.

definition: The acronym of the name assigned by the Institution (project leader or principal investigator) to the project, from which the source data originates from.
The name assigned by the Institution (project leader or principal investigator) to the project from which the source data originates from.
Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing location data for the Integrated Stream Habitat Data. This table corresponds to the Location table in the database (.accdb) file.
A unique numeric identifier assigned to the originating source data's program.
An identifier for the set of location information. Global unique identifier.
The verbatim location ID from the originating source dataset assigned by the monitoring program.
The geographic latitude (WGS84) of the geographic center of a location in decimal degrees.
The geographic longitude (WGS84) of the geographic center of a location in decimal degrees.
Comments or notes about the Location. The location along the reach where geographic coordinates were obtained.
The type of site selection used according to the program.
NAdefinition: Site selection not known or reported by the program.

definition: The name of the water body in which the Location occurs.
NAdefinition: Water body name not reported in the original dataset.

definition: Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing Event data for the Integrated Stream Habitat Data. This table corresponds to the Event table in the database (.accdb) file.
Unique global identifier assigned to the location where the event occurred.
The calendar date during which an Event occurred.
NAdefinition: Source data from AREMP do not contain month or day, so no there is no eventDate for those entries.

definition: An identifier for the set of information associated with an Event (something that occurs at a place and time). Global unique identifier.
The description of flow for the reach.
NAdefinition: Description of the flow was not included or reported in the source dataset.
noteAndConventions: Assigned Categories: Flow (Whole Reach); No Flow Dry; Other

definition: The names of, references to, or descriptions of the methods or protocols used during an Event.
The verbatim event ID from the originating source dataset assigned by the program.
noteAndConventions: from source datasets converted to string. Reference to source datasets unique identifier for location data.

definition: Beaver impact on the flow of the reach.
NAdefinition: Beaver impacts were not reported in the source data.
noteAndConventions: Assigned categories: Major; Minor; None; NA

definition: The four-digit year in which the Event occurred, according to the Common Era Calendar.
Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing MeasurementorFact data for the Integrated Stream Habitat Data. This table corresponds to the MeasurementorFact table in the database (.accdb) file.
An identifier for the set of information associated with an Event (something that occurs at a place and time). Global unique identifier.
Unique identifier assigned to the measurementValue.
The nature of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
Unique identifier assigned to the measurementType.
The value of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.

Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing the data map between the original source dataset field names and the integrated dataset fields. References to the collection and analysis methods used by the originating monitoring programs are also included. This table corresponds to the DataMapping table in the database (.accdb) file.

Unique identifier assigned to the term. IDs ranging in the 200s are for terms present in the Location table, 300s are for terms in the Event table, 401 denotes a measurementType, and 500s are for terms in the MeasurementOrFact table (assigned based on a term's first apperance within a table).
A column or field header included in at least one table within the integrated dataset.
Unique identifier assigned to the measurementType.
NAdefinition: There is no measurementType associated with this term so there is no measurementTypeID.

definition: The nature of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
NAdefinition: There is no measurementType associated with this term.

definition: The type of data valid for the term or measurementType as read by computer software.
The acronym assigned to the monitoring program from which the term or measurementType originated.

The original name assigned to the term in the Source Data. Further information about the originalField can be found in the source data's metadata (if available) referenced in the Record table under metadataID.
NAdefinition: The term is not present in the Source Data and/or the term was not included in the Integrated Dataset due to a lack of compatibility across program so there is no original field to report.

definition: The original units associated with the term or measurementType in the Source Data. Further information about the originalUnit can be found in the source data's metadata (if available) referenced in the Record table under metadataID.
NAdefinition: Units are not associated with this originalField or the originalField was NA so there are no relevant units.

definition: The original type of data as read by computer software which is valid for a term or measurementType in the Source Data.
URL for the originating Source Data collection method used on-site in the field to obtain the value for the measurementType.
NAdefinition: The term is not present in the Source Data and/or the term was not included in the Integrated Dataset due to a lack of compatibility across programs so the CollectionMethod is not included here. Refer to Completeness in the metadata record for additional information on what Source Data were and were not included in the integrated dataset.

definition: URL for the originating Source Data analysis method used on-site in the field and/or lab to obtain the value for the measurementType.
NAdefinition: The term is not present in the Source Data and/or the term was not included in the Integrated Dataset due to a lack of compatibility across programs so the AnalysisMethod is not included here. Refer to Completeness in the metadata record for additional information on what Source Data were and were not included in the integrated dataset.

definition: Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing the controlled vocabulary (with definitions) used to integrate the dataset for the Stream Habitat Metric Integration project. This table corresponds to the MetricControlledVocabulary table in the database (.accdb) file.

Unique identifier assigned to the term. IDs ranging in the 200s are for terms present in the Location table, 300s are for terms in the Event table, 401 denotes a measurementType, and 500s are for terms in the MeasurementOrFact table (assigned based on a term's first apperance within a table).
A column or field header included in at least one table within the integrated dataset.
Unique identifier assigned to the measurementType.
The nature of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
The definition for the measurementType.
The valid unit of measurement associated with the measurementType.
NAdefinition: Measurement units are not applicable to this measurementType.

definition: The type of data valid for the measurementType as read by computer software.
The table to which the term belongs.
The minimum possible legal value for this measurementType.
The maximum possible legal value for this measurementType.
NAdefinition: Maximum values are not applicable to this measurementType.
